# Database Migrations

The Housekeeper service is the single owner of all database migrations.

These rules mirror the migration conventions of the paymentgate project.

## Ownership

* All migrations live under `src/housekeeper/migrations/`.
* All migrations are generated and applied exclusively through Housekeeper.
* No other service may create, run, or own migrations.
* `alembic.ini` lives at `src/housekeeper/alembic.ini`.

## Per-service segregation

* Migrations are segregated per service/database into subdirectories:
  `src/housekeeper/migrations/<service>/`.
* Each service/database has its own revision history; never mix services in one
  directory.

## Alembic configuration (multi-database)

* The `[alembic]` section declares every database:
  `databases = patients, ml, rag` (comma-separated list of all logical DBs).
* `[DEFAULT]` holds the shared `file_template` and `truncate_slug_length = 60`.
* Each database has its own section with a per-service version location:

```ini
[patients]
sqlalchemy.url = driver://user:pass@localhost/dbname
version_locations = ./migrations/patients
```

* Global keys: `prepend_sys_path = .`, `script_location = ./migrations/`,
  `version_path_separator = os`.

## Migration file naming (mandatory)

* Use the timestamp-prefixed template exactly:

```ini
file_template = %%(year)d-%%(month).2d-%%(day).2d-%%(hour).2d-%%(minute).2d-%%(second).2d-%%(rev)s_%%(slug)s
```

* This produces filenames like:

```
2026-02-03-22-42-50-ced76f42edaa_.py
```

  i.e. `YYYY-MM-DD-HH-MM-SS-<revision_hash>_<slug>.py` (slug may be empty).
* Keep `truncate_slug_length = 60`.

## env.py behavior

* Select the active database from the ini section: `db_name = config.config_ini_section`.
* Import that service's model metadata dynamically and use its `Base.metadata`
  as `target_metadata`.
* Read the database URL from settings keyed by db name
  (e.g. `settings.<db_name>_postgres_uri`), escaping `%` as `%%`.
* Skip revision generation when there are no changes
  (`process_revision_directives`), logging a warning.
* Filter reflected objects not described in the models (`include_object`).
* Run with the async engine, falling back to a sync engine when greenlet is
  unavailable (local environment).

## Workflow

* Generate and apply migrations per service by selecting its ini section:

```bash
alembic -n <service> revision --autogenerate -m "message"
alembic -n <service> upgrade head
```

* Wrap these in Housekeeper Make targets; never invoke migrations from another
  service.

