# Service lifecycle (Makefile)

Every service is started and stopped through Makefile targets defined in the
repo-root `Makefile`. Do not document or use ad-hoc `docker compose` / `uvicorn`
invocations when an equivalent Make target exists.

## Per-service up / down (Docker)

* Bring a single service up: `make up_<abbr>` (uses `infra/application.compose.yml`)
* Tear a single service down: `make down_<abbr>`
* Each target wraps `docker compose -f infra/application.compose.yml` for that
  service only.
* Postgres lives in `infra/infra.compose.yml`; run `make up_infra` before app
  services so the shared `neuroatlasnet` network and database are available.

## Infra vs application compose

* `infra/infra.compose.yml` — infrastructure only (Postgres, shared network).
  Targets: `make up_infra`, `make down_infra`.
* `infra/application.compose.yml` — application services only (patients, ml,
  housekeeper). Targets: `make up_app`, `make down_app`, and all
  `up_<abbr>` / `down_<abbr>` targets.
* Migrations are **not** a compose service. Apply them explicitly with
  `make migrate` (after `make up_infra`) or per-service `alembic -n <service>`
  once the multi-db layout lands.

## Service abbreviations (mandatory)

Use these short codes in Make target names:

| Service      | Abbreviation | Up            | Down              |
|--------------|--------------|---------------|-------------------|
| patients     | `pat`        | `make up_pat` | `make down_pat`   |
| ml           | `ml`         | `make up_ml`  | `make down_ml`    |
| housekeeper  | `hk`         | `make up_hk`  | `make down_hk`    |
| rag          | `rag`        | `make up_rag` | `make down_rag`   |

When adding a new service, register its abbreviation in this table and add
matching `up_<abbr>` / `down_<abbr>` targets to the `Makefile`.

## Full stack

* `make up` — start infra then app (`up_infra` + `up_app`).
* `make down` — stop app then infra (`down_app` + `down_infra`).
* `make up_infra` / `make down_infra` — Postgres + `neuroatlasnet` only.
* `make up_app` / `make down_app` — all application services.

Use per-service targets for day-to-day work; use `make up` / `make down` when
you need the entire environment. Always ensure infra is up before starting app
services.

## Local run (no Docker)

* Run a service locally with hot reload: `make run_<service>` (full service name,
  not abbreviation), e.g. `make run_patients`, `make run_ml`, `make run_housekeeper`.
* Local run targets use `uvicorn` and do not require Docker; they are for
  development against in-memory adapters or a locally running Postgres.

## Naming rules

* Docker lifecycle: `up_<abbr>` / `down_<abbr>` (short abbreviation).
* Local dev server: `run_<service>` (full service directory name).
* Tests: `test_<service>` (full service directory name).
* New services must follow all three patterns in the `Makefile`.
